5000|$|Mercuric amidochloride is an {{inorganic}} compound with the formula <b>HgNH2Cl.</b> It {{consists of a}} zig-zag 1-dimensional polymer (HgNH2)n with chloride counterions. It arises from the reaction of ammonia and mercuric chloride. Addition of base converts it into [...] "Millon's base," [...] which has the formula Hg2NOH(H2O)x. A variety of related amido and nitrido materials with chloride, bromide, and hydroxide are known.|$|E

